----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNA  Service String Advice

    Function: To define the characters selected for use as delimiters and indicators in the rest of the interchange that follows.

Ref  Name                              M/C  Repr.   Remarks

    COMPONENT DATA ELEMENT SEPARATOR   M    an1
    DATA ELEMENT SEPARATOR             M    an1
    DECIMAL NOTATION                   M    an1     Comma or full stop
    RELEASE INDICATOR                  M    an1     If not used, insert space character
    Reserved for future use            M    an1     Insert space character
    SEGMENT TERMINATOR                 M    an1
 
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNB  Interchange Header

    Function: To start, identify and specify an interchange

Ref  Name                          M/C  Repr.       Remarks

S001 SYNTAX IDENTIFIER                 M
0001   Syntax identifier               M   a4       a3, upper case, Controlling Agency (e.g. UNO = UN/ECE) and a1 stating level (e.g. A)
0002   Syntax version number           M   n1       Increments 1 for each new version. Shall be 2 to indicate this version

S002 INTERCHANGE SENDER                M
0004   Sender identification           M   an..35   Code or name as specified in IA
0007   Identification code qualifier   C   an..4    Used with sender identification code
0008   Address for reverse routing     C   an..14

S003 INTERCHANGE RECIPIENT             M
0010   Recipient Identification        M   an..35   Code or name as specified in IA
0007   Identification code qualifier   C   an..4    Used with recipient identification code
0014   Routing address                 C   an..14   If used, normally coded sub-address for onward routing

S004 DATE/TIME OF PREPARATION          M
0017   Date                            M   n6       Format: YYMMDD
0019   Time                            M   n4       Format: HHMM

0020 INTERCHANGE CONTROL REFERENCE     M   an..14   Unique reference assigned by sender

S005  RECIPIENTS REFERENCE, PASSWORD   C
0022    Recipient's reference/password  M  an..14     As specified in IA. May be password to recipient's system or to third party network
0025    Recipient's reference/password qualifier  C  an2       If specified in IA

0026  APPLICATION REFERENCE            C  an..14     Optionally message identification if the interchange contains only one type of message

0029  PROCESSING PRIORITY CODE         C  a1         Used if specified in IA

0031  ACKNOWLEDGEMENT REQUEST          C  n1         Set = 1 if sender requests acknowledgement, i.e. UNB and UNZ segments received and identified

0032  COMMUNICATIONS AGREEMENT ID      C  an..35   If used, to identify type of communication agreement controlling the interchange, e.g. Customs or ECE agreement. Code or name as specified in IA

0035 TEST INDICATOR                    C  n1         Set = 1 if the interchange is a test. Otherwise not used

----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNZ  Interchange Trailer

    Function: To end and check the completeness of an interchange

Ref  Name                          M/C  Repr.   Remarks

0036 INTERCHANGE CONTROL COUNT           M   n..6

0020 INTERCHANGE CONTROL REFERENCE       M   an..14

