    UNG  Functional Group Header

    Function: To head, identify and specify a Functional Group

Ref  Name                                    M/C  Repr.   Remarks

0038 FUNCTIONAL GROUP IDENTIFICATION         M   an..6    Identifies the one message type in the functional group

S006 APPLICATION SENDER'S IDENTIFICATION     M
0040   Sender identification                 M  an..35
0007   Sender identification qualifier       C  an..4

S007 APPLICATION RECIPIENTS IDENTIFICATION   M
0044   Recipient's identification            M  an..35 Code or name identifying the division, department etc. within the recipients organization for which the group of messages is intended
0007   Recipient's identification qualifier  C  an..4  May be used if recipient identification is a code

S004 DATE/TIME OF PREPARATION                M
0017   Date                                  M  n6     Format: YYMMDD
0019   Time                                  M  n4     Format: HHMM

0048 FUNCTIONAL GROUP REFERENCE NUMBER       M  an..14 Unique reference number assigned by sender's division, department etc.

0051 CONTROLLING AGENCY                      M  an..2 Code to identify the agency controlling the specification, maintenance and publication of the message type

S008 MESSAGE VERSION                         M
0052   Message version number                M  an..3   Version number of the message type in the functional group
0054   Message release number                M  an..3   Release number within current version number
0057   Association assigned Code             C  an..6   A code assigned by the association responsible for the design and maintenance of the type of message concerned

0058 APPLICATION PASSWORD                     C  an..14  Password to recipient's division, department or sectional system (if required)

----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNE  Functional Group Trailer

    Function: To end and check the completeness of a Functional Group

Ref  Name                                M/C  Repr.   Remarks

0060 NUMBER OF MESSAGES                  M    n..6    The count of the number of messages in the functional group
0048 FUNCTIONAL GROUP REFERENCE NUMBER   M    an..14  Shall be identical to 0048 in UNG

----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNH  Message Header

    Function: To head, identify and specify a Message

Ref  Name                                 M/C  Repr.   Remarks

0062 MESSAGE REFERENCE NUMBER             M   an..14

S009 MESSAGE IDENTIFIER                   M
0065   Message type                       M   an..6   Type of message being transmitted
0052   Message version number             M   an..3   Version number of the message type. If UNG is used, 0052 shall be identical
0054   Message release number             M   an..3   Release number within current version number
0051   Controlling agency                 M   an..2   Code to identify the agency controlling the specification, maintenance and publication of the message type
0057   Association assigned code          C   an..6   A code assigned by the association responsible for the design and maintenance of the message type

0068 COMMON ACCESS REFERENCE              C  an..35   to relate all subsequent transfers of data to the same business case or file. Within the 35 characters the IA may specify component elements

S010 STATUS OF THE TRANSFER               C
0070   Sequence of transfers              M   n..2
0073   First and last transfer            C   a1    C = Creation, must be present for first transfer if more than one foreseen; F = Final, must be present for last transfer
 
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNT  Message Trailer

    Function: To end and check the completeness of a Message

Ref  Name                                 M/C  Repr.    Remarks

0074 NUMBER OF SEGMENTS IN THE MESSAGE    M    n..6     Control count including UNH and UNT

0062 MESSAGE REFERENCE NUMBER             M    an..14   Shall be identical to 0062 in UNH

----------------------------------------------------------------------

    TXT  Text

    Function: To give information in addition to that in other segments in the service message, as required


    NOTE: Can not be machine processed. Should be avoided if not necessarily required.
          Normally a conditional segment.
          It may repeat up to the number of times indicated in the message
          specification which may not be higher than 5.

Ref  Name                                   M/C  Repr.   Remarks

0077 TEXT REFERENCE CODE                    C  an3     Qualifies and identifies the purpose and function of the segment if indicated in the message specification

0078 FREE FORM TEXT                         M an..70   Not machine-processable information

----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNS  Section Control

    Function: To separate Header, Detail and Summary sections of a message

    NOTE: To be used by message designers when required to avoid ambiguities.
              Mandatory only if specified for the type of message concerned.

Ref  Name                                   M/C  Repr.   Remarks

0081    SECTION IDENTIFICATION              M   a1    Separates sections in a message by one of the following codes: D separates the header and detail sections; S separates the detail and summary sections


----------------------------------------------------------------------

    UNT  Message Trailer

    Function: To end and check the completeness of a Message

Ref  Name                                   M/C  Repr.   Remarks

0074 NUMBER OF SEGMENTS IN THE MESSAGE  M  n..6    Control count including UNH and UNT
0062 MESSAGE REFERENCE NUMBER           M  an..14  Shall be identical to 0062 in UNH

